<HL>
   Business Brief -- Modine Manufacturing Co.:
   Agreement to Acquire Unit
   Of Sundstrand Is Signed
</HL>
<DATE>
07/19/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MODI SNS
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Modine Manufacturing Co. said it signed an agreement in
principle to purchase the heat transfer operations of
Rockford, Ill.-based Sundstrand Corp. Terms weren't
disclosed.
   The Racine, Wis., company said the sale is subject to the
approval of a definitive agreement, approval of the directors
of the companies, and to other customary conditions.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Earl E. Richter, chairman and chief executive officer,
said the acquisition will "increase annual sales by 15% to
20%." Modine earned $25.2 million, or $1.68 a share, on sales
of $436.3 million in the fiscal year ended March 31, 1990.
   The maker of automotive parts and heating and
air-conditioning equipment said that through the acquisition
it will enter into markets it doesn't now serve.
</TEXT>
